I have very few IRL friends on Twitter - that's what FB & IG are for. But Twitter has made my life richer and more interesting, and I hate to lose it. /end

There's also the dark side where, for example, horrible people make fun of an elderly man getting bashed in the head with a hammer. I think twitter is where I really understood that the world is full of psychopaths, and asking "aren't you ashamed of yourself?" means nothing. 4/

The other day there was a long thread where people shared the last moments of their loved ones lives. It was poignant and hopeful and made me cry in a good way. 
3/

And then there's the occasional thread that makes me laugh out loud, or cry, or feel hopeful; that's witty and punny and each reply is funnier than the previous. Letters From the Second Civil War was the best thing I've ever seen on the internet. 2/

What I love about Twitter is that it's egalitarian. Very few people have restricted accounts. I follow constitutional lawyers, artists, musicians, pundits, journalists, none of whom know me, but I can contribute to the conversations and maybe even make a difference. 1/
